WEBVTT

00:04.838 --> 00:05.806 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening.

00:05.839 --> 00:06.773 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:06.807 --> 00:08.709 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
On the "NewsHour" tonight:

00:08.742 --> 00:12.779 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JAMES COMEY, FBI Director: Our
counterintelligence
mission is investing the Russian
government's

00:12.813 --> 00:16.617 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
efforts to interfere in the 2016
presidential
election.

00:16.650 --> 00:23.056 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: FBI Director
James Comey confirms
a probe into Russian meddling,
including possible

00:23.090 --> 00:28.228 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
links between Moscow and the
Trump campaign,
while saying there's no evidence
for the president's

00:28.262 --> 00:30.063 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
charge he was wiretapped.

00:30.097 --> 00:36.069 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
In our other lead story:
President Trump's
Supreme Court nominee, Judge
Neil Gorsuch,

00:36.103 --> 00:40.007 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
faces the Senate Judiciary
Committee on the
first day of confirmation
hearings.

00:40.040 --> 00:46.079 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NEIL GORSUCH, Supreme Court
Nominee: Ninety-seven
percent of those 2,700 cases I
have decided

00:46.113 --> 00:52.886 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
were decided unanimously, and
that I have
been in the majority 99 percent
of the time.

00:52.920 --> 00:56.056 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That's my record and that's how
we do things
in the West.

00:56.089 --> 01:02.029 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And from the
items in a market
to celebrating work, how one art
exhibit is

01:02.062 --> 01:06.667 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
defining the nature of home here
in the U.S.
for Latino Americans.

01:06.700 --> 01:09.369 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
RAMIRO GOMEZ, Artist: So, I'm at
once Mexican
and American.

01:09.403 --> 01:11.204 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I'm in between.

01:11.238 --> 01:17.010 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That in-between space, that
in-between place
that I occupy is something that
is constantly

01:17.044 --> 01:18.278 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
changing within myself.

01:18.312 --> 01:21.648 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All that and more
on tonight's
"PBS NewsHour."

01:21.682 --> 01:24.818 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

01:24.851 --> 01:39.099 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: An unusually
newsy day in the
nation's capital, even by
Washington standards,

01:39.132 --> 01:45.272 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that make up our two leads: A
House committee
delves into a possible Russian
role in the

01:45.305 --> 01:50.644 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
campaign that elected Donald
Trump, and a
Senate panel begins hearings on
the man chosen

01:50.677 --> 01:54.014 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
by President Trump to serve on
the Supreme
Court.

01:54.047 --> 01:59.419 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We begin with the Russia file,
and Lisa Desjardins,
who has been watching it all.

01:59.453 --> 02:07.027 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: In a rare open
hearing of
the House Intelligence
Committee, a rare admission

02:07.060 --> 02:08.929 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
from the FBI director.

02:08.962 --> 02:12.132 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JAMES COMEY, FBI Director: I
have been authorized
by the Department of Justice to
confirm that

02:12.165 --> 02:18.638 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
the FBI, as part of our
counterintelligence
mission, is investigating the
Russian government's

02:18.672 --> 02:23.410 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
efforts to interfere in the 2016
presidential
election.

02:23.443 --> 02:28.849 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that includes investigating
the nature
of any links between individuals
associated

02:28.882 --> 02:35.288 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
with the Trump campaign and the
Russian government
and whether there was any
coordination between

02:35.322 --> 02:37.290 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the campaign and Russia's
efforts.

02:37.324 --> 02:42.529 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Beside Comey
sat National
Security Agency Chief Michael
Rogers.

02:42.562 --> 02:47.167 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Both stood by the intelligence
community's
earlier report that Russian
President Vladimir

02:47.200 --> 02:50.504 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Putin clearly favored the
candidacy of Donald
Trump.

02:50.537 --> 02:56.343 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JAMES COMEY: Putin hated
Secretary Clinton
so much, that the flip side of
that coin was

02:56.376 --> 02:59.980 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
he had a clear preference for
the person running
against the person he hated so
much.

03:00.013 --> 03:04.251 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Committee
Democrats and Republicans
pursued sharply different lines
of questioning:

03:04.284 --> 03:06.086 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

03:06.119 --> 03:08.889 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ADAM SCHIFF (D), California: In
early July,
Carter Page, someone candidate
Trump identified

03:08.922 --> 03:13.894 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
as one of his national security
advisers,
travels to Moscow on a trip
approved by the

03:13.927 --> 03:15.695 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Trump campaign.

03:15.729 --> 03:19.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
LISA DESJARDINS: Ranking
Democrat Adam Schiff
listed contacts between Trump
advisers and

03:19.666 --> 03:21.935 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Russian officials and raised
concern.

03:21.968 --> 03:23.770 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

03:23.804 --> 03:26.907 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ADAM SCHIFF: Many of Trump
campaign personnel,
including the president himself,
have ties

03:26.940 --> 03:29.543 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
to Russia and Russian interests.

03:29.576 --> 03:32.379 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
This is, of course, no crime.

03:32.412 --> 03:37.784 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
On the other hand, if the Trump
campaign or
anyone associated with it aided
or abetted

03:37.818 --> 03:40.687 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the Russians, it wouldn't only
be a serious
crime.

03:40.720 --> 03:45.092 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It would also represent one of
the most shocking
betrayals of democracy in
history.

03:45.125 --> 03:49.629 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: But committee
Chairman Devin
Nunes and other Republicans
pushed to show

03:49.663 --> 03:52.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that Russians didn't directly
change vote
totals.

03:52.799 --> 03:54.701 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

03:54.734 --> 03:56.570 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DEVIN NUNES (R), California:
Admiral Rogers,
do you have any evidence that
Russia cyber-actors

03:56.603 --> 03:58.305 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
changed vote tallies?

03:58.338 --> 03:59.606 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
ADM.

03:59.639 --> 04:01.408 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MIKE ROGERS, National Security
Agency Director:
No, I do not.

04:01.441 --> 04:05.545 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: The president
soon after
tweeted that: "The NSA and FBI
tell Congress

04:05.579 --> 04:09.149 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that Russia didn't influence
electoral process."

04:09.182 --> 04:14.321 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, back at the hearing,
Democrat Jim Himes
pounced, saying a lack of
manipulating votes

04:14.354 --> 04:17.290 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
directly is different than no
influence at
all.

04:17.324 --> 04:19.059 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

04:19.092 --> 04:20.794 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JIM HIMES (D), Connecticut: So,
it's not too
far of a logical leap to
conclude that the

04:20.827 --> 04:26.133 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
assertion that you have told the
Congress
that there was no influence on
the electoral

04:26.166 --> 04:27.234 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
is not quite right?

04:27.267 --> 04:29.069 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JAMES COMEY: Right.

04:29.102 --> 04:32.038 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
It certainly wasn't our
intention to say that
today, because we don't have any
information

04:32.072 --> 04:33.573 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
on that subject.

04:33.607 --> 04:35.609 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That's not something that was
looked at.

04:35.642 --> 04:40.180 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: More than
anything, Republicans
raised alarm over leaks and
stories with reportedly

04:40.213 --> 04:43.083 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
classified information and names
in the investigation.

04:43.116 --> 04:44.951 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

04:44.985 --> 04:48.421 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TREY GOWDY (R), South Carolina:
I thought
it was against the law to
disseminate classified

04:48.455 --> 04:49.422 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
information.

04:49.456 --> 04:50.724 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Is it?

04:50.757 --> 04:53.827 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JAMES COMEY: Oh, yes.

04:53.860 --> 04:56.363 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Sure, it's a serious crime.

04:56.396 --> 05:00.867 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: South Carolina
Congressman
Trey Gowdy went farther, warning
that unless

05:00.901 --> 05:05.238 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the leaks are stopped, a key
provision of
the Foreign Intelligence
Surveillance Act,

05:05.272 --> 05:08.875 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
or FISA, may not be reauthorized
by Congress
this year.

05:08.909 --> 05:10.243 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

05:10.277 --> 05:12.245 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TREY GOWDY: Trust me, you and I
both want
to see it reauthorized.

05:12.279 --> 05:14.814 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's in jeopardy if we don't get
this resolved.

05:14.848 --> 05:18.418 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: The hearing hit
extraordinary
territory.

05:18.451 --> 05:23.089 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Democrats pushed on President
Trump's charges
that President Obama wiretapped
him.

05:23.123 --> 05:27.227 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JAMES COMEY: With respect to the
presidents
tweets about alleged wiretapping
directed

05:27.260 --> 05:31.765 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
at him by the prior
administration, I have
no information that supports
those tweets.

05:31.798 --> 05:36.469 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Republican
Chairman Nunes
agreed, but didn't rule out that
other measures

05:36.503 --> 05:37.470 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
could have been involved.

05:37.504 --> 05:39.206 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

05:39.239 --> 05:41.508 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DEVIN NUNES: It's still possible
that other
surveillance activities were
used against

05:41.541 --> 05:44.110 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
President Trump and his
associates.

05:44.144 --> 05:48.114 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: President Trump
and his aides
have refused to back off the
surveillance

05:48.148 --> 05:49.482 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
charge.

05:49.516 --> 05:52.085 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They say it's veracity is for
the investigation
to determine.

05:52.118 --> 05:57.490 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Meanwhile, today, White House
spokesman Sean
Spicer defended the president
and his campaign,

05:57.524 --> 06:02.963 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
but he also seemed to downplay
the campaign
role of two key players known
for their ties

06:02.996 --> 06:08.635 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to Russia, former campaign
adviser Michael
Flynn and former campaign
manager Paul Manafort.

06:08.668 --> 06:12.272 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SEAN SPICER, White House Press
Secretary:
Even General Flynn was a
volunteer of the

06:12.305 --> 06:14.074 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
campaign.

06:14.107 --> 06:17.777 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And then, obviously, there's
been discussion
of Paul Manafort, who played a
very limited

06:17.811 --> 06:19.879 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
role for a very limited amount
of time.

06:19.913 --> 06:25.719 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: At the hearing,
over it all
was Russia, a country the NSA
chief said changed

06:25.752 --> 06:26.987 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
its tactics in 2016.

06:27.020 --> 06:28.989 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
ADM.

06:29.022 --> 06:33.526 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MIKE ROGERS: I would say the
biggest difference,
from my perspective, was both
the use of cyber,

06:33.560 --> 06:40.934 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the hacking as a vehicle to
physically gain
access, to information to
extract that information

06:40.967 --> 06:45.305 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and then to make it widely
publicly available
without any alteration or
change.

06:45.338 --> 06:49.276 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JAMES COMEY: The only thing that
I would add
is that they were unusually loud
in their

06:49.309 --> 06:51.077 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
intervention.

06:51.111 --> 06:54.314 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's almost as if they didn't
care that we
knew what they were doing or
that they wanted

06:54.347 --> 06:55.782 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
us to see what they were doing.

06:55.815 --> 06:58.051 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: FBI Director
Comey gave a
warning.

06:58.084 --> 06:59.486 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JAMES COMEY: They will be back.

06:59.519 --> 07:01.554 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They will be back in 2020.

07:01.588 --> 07:04.190 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They may be back in 2018.

07:04.224 --> 07:08.161 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And one of the lessons they may
draw from
this is that they were
successful, because

07:08.194 --> 07:10.797 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
they introduced chaos and
division and discord.

07:10.830 --> 07:15.535 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Chairman Nunes
closed the
hearing with a stark verdict on
the five-hour

07:15.568 --> 07:16.536 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
session.

07:16.569 --> 07:18.305 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

07:18.338 --> 07:20.974 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DEVIN NUNES: There is a big,
gray cloud that
you have now put over people who
have very

07:21.007 --> 07:23.443 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
important work to do to lead
this country.

07:23.476 --> 07:29.482 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so the faster you can get to
the bottom
of this, it's going to be better
for all Americans.

07:29.516 --> 07:33.687 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: For "PBS
NewsHour," I'm Lisa
Desjardins at the Capitol.

07:33.720 --> 07:38.091 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And we turn now
to the ranking
member of the House Intelligence
Committee.

07:38.124 --> 07:41.828 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He is Democratic Representative
Adam Schiff
of California.

07:41.861 --> 07:44.197 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Congressman Schiff, welcome back
to the program.

07:44.230 --> 07:47.534 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What's the main thing that you
think was clarified
at today's hearing?

07:47.567 --> 07:48.568 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

07:48.601 --> 07:50.537 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ADAM SCHIFF: Well, I think a
number of things.

07:50.570 --> 07:57.410 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
First, I think Director Comey
made the case
that he had opened an
investigation into potential

07:57.444 --> 08:02.449 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
agency with a foreign power or
coordination
with a foreign power.

08:02.482 --> 08:07.220 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That's not done unless there is
specific and
credible information or evidence
that someone

08:07.253 --> 08:08.888 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
is colluding.

08:08.922 --> 08:13.493 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
I also think that it was
significant that
you had two directors directly
rebuff the

08:13.526 --> 08:19.099 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
president's claims that he was
illegally wiretapped
or wiretapped at all by his
predecessor.

08:19.132 --> 08:24.204 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But more than that, I think the
main takeaway,
I hope, for the country from the
hearing is

08:24.237 --> 08:28.675 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a recognition of just what
serious business
this is, because, as Director
Comey says,

08:28.708 --> 08:30.777 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the Russians will do this again.

08:30.810 --> 08:35.081 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And we really need a thorough
investigation
to determine just what the
Russians did, how

08:35.115 --> 08:39.853 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
did they do it, were there U.S.
persons involved,
and how do we protect ourselves
from their

08:39.886 --> 08:41.621 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
future efforts to interfere?

08:41.654 --> 08:46.826 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, I hear you
say this,
Congressman Schiff, and yet
President Trump

08:46.860 --> 08:54.667 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
tweeted today that Admiral
Rogers and the
FBI director, Jim Comey, told
Congress that

08:54.701 --> 08:59.773 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Russia didn't influence the
electoral process
in the United States last year.

08:59.806 --> 09:02.409 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, that doesn't seem to square
with what
you just said.

09:02.442 --> 09:04.177 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

09:04.210 --> 09:06.379 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ADAM SCHIFF: Well, it didn't
square with what
the witnesses said at the
hearing either.

09:06.413 --> 09:10.517 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And that was pointed by my
colleague Jim Himes,
who followed up with both
directors and did

09:10.550 --> 09:13.052 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
some real-time fact-checking on
the president.

09:13.086 --> 09:14.954 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, of course, that's not what
the directors
said.

09:14.988 --> 09:17.023 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The directors can't really
comment.

09:17.056 --> 09:22.295 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's not their mission, their
job or their
expertise to say what effect the
Russian interference

09:22.328 --> 09:27.934 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
had in terms of outcomes, but
clearly they
interfered with the electoral
process.

09:27.967 --> 09:29.736 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And here's the problem.

09:29.769 --> 09:35.508 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If the president is going to
distort what
the intelligence community says
in open hearing,

09:35.542 --> 09:39.612 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
how can we have confidence when
the president
comes before the country to
share what the

09:39.646 --> 09:44.584 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
intelligence agencies have told
him in closed,
classified session, because the
country needs

09:44.617 --> 09:48.988 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to know, because the president
wants to take
action, where the president
needs to decide

09:49.022 --> 09:52.959 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
what the response should be to
North Korea
or around Iran?

09:52.992 --> 09:55.862 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
How can we have confidence that
the president
is being truthful?

09:55.895 --> 09:59.799 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And the short answer is, if he
keeps this
up, we can't.

09:59.833 --> 10:01.167 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And that's a real danger to the
country.

10:01.201 --> 10:06.005 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, what does
that mean,
Congressman Schiff?

10:06.039 --> 10:08.341 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What are you saying you're
worried that could
happen?

10:08.374 --> 10:10.176 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

10:10.210 --> 10:12.679 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ADAM SCHIFF: Well, the best
example I can
give is, let's say, six months
from now, the

10:12.712 --> 10:15.315 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
president says that Iran is
cheating on the
nuclear deal.

10:15.348 --> 10:18.785 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Obviously, if Iran isn't
cheating, that's
a big problem.

10:18.818 --> 10:23.323 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If he's making this up, the way
he's making
up the claim that Barack Obama
wiretapped

10:23.356 --> 10:25.124 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
him, that's a big problem.

10:25.158 --> 10:29.696 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If the president is telling the
truth, in
a way, it's a bigger problem,
because, will

10:29.729 --> 10:31.397 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
he be believed?

10:31.431 --> 10:33.199 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Will he be believed by the
American people?

10:33.233 --> 10:37.704 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Will he be believed by our
allies that he
needs to rally to reimpose
sanctions or take

10:37.737 --> 10:40.039 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
some other action against Iran?

10:40.073 --> 10:45.078 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Each time the president
undermines his own
credibility, he weakens himself,
he weakens

10:45.111 --> 10:49.215 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
the institution of the
presidency, he weakens
the credibility of the entire
country and

10:49.249 --> 10:51.017 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
our standing in the rest of the
world.

10:51.050 --> 10:54.888 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And when there is a crisis, we
pay a dear
price for that loss of
credibility.

10:54.921 --> 10:59.392 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: On the other
hand, Congressman,
Republicans on the committee
today were calling

10:59.425 --> 11:03.263 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
into question whether the
intelligence community
can be relied on.

11:03.296 --> 11:07.834 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They -- question after question
was about
leaks coming from the
intelligence community

11:07.867 --> 11:11.538 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and anyone who had access to
that information.

11:11.571 --> 11:16.543 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The president, President Trump,
is saying
what the intelligence community
says is fake

11:16.576 --> 11:17.544 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
news.

11:17.577 --> 11:19.646 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
He's dismissing it.

11:19.679 --> 11:23.182 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Republicans are saying they're
leaking all
over the place.

11:23.216 --> 11:28.821 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, I guess my question -- and
then you also
had Congressman Trey Gowdy, your
Republican

11:28.855 --> 11:33.593 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
colleague on the committee,
saying that perhaps
the FISA court, the courts that
authorize

11:33.626 --> 11:38.131 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
much of their investigation, may
be in trouble.

11:38.164 --> 11:42.168 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Are you confident that an
investigation is
going to be thoroughly carried
out here?

11:42.201 --> 11:43.937 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

11:43.970 --> 11:46.372 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ADAM SCHIFF: Well, on the leak
issue, first
of all, I think we have to
understand just

11:46.406 --> 11:49.242 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the breadth of what people are
talking about
when they talk about leaks.

11:49.275 --> 11:53.913 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The leaks that most concern me,
that ought
to most concern the country is
when information

11:53.947 --> 12:01.187 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
is leaked that betrays sources
and methods
of information that our allies
-- well, that

12:01.220 --> 12:06.926 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
expose us to danger, because our
enemies can
then perpetrate attacks because
we lose those

12:06.960 --> 12:09.195 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
confidential sources of
information.

12:09.228 --> 12:11.064 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Those are the most serious
leaks.

12:11.097 --> 12:14.934 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What seems to really upset the
administration
is a different kind of leak.

12:14.968 --> 12:18.571 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
It's a leak that exposes
malfeasance within
the administration.

12:18.605 --> 12:23.209 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What really upset the president
wasn't the
fact that Mike Flynn was
unmasked to the country

12:23.242 --> 12:29.382 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and that Mike Flynn was exposed
as having
lied to the country and the vice
president

12:29.415 --> 12:31.985 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
about his conversations with the
Russian ambassador.

12:32.018 --> 12:35.888 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What really upset the president
was that,
essentially, he was caught in
the lie.

12:35.922 --> 12:40.526 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And you will remember, even
after firing Flynn,
he wanted to praise Flynn and
castigate the

12:40.560 --> 12:41.527 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
press.

12:41.561 --> 12:42.895 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
That's something very different.

12:42.929 --> 12:47.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That's a leak that discloses
malfeasance in
the administration.

12:47.133 --> 12:51.571 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I would say, look, this leak
problem,
every administration has it.

12:51.604 --> 12:55.675 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And one of the things my GOP
colleagues didn't
want to acknowledge today -- and
the president

12:55.708 --> 13:00.346 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
certainly doesn't want to
acknowledge -- is,
they can say we think, we fear,
we suspect

13:00.380 --> 13:03.016 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
this is coming from the
intelligence community.

13:03.049 --> 13:04.384 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They're a bunch of Nazis.

13:04.417 --> 13:08.187 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
That's essentially the
president's original
tweet on this.

13:08.221 --> 13:13.860 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But it's also very possible that
some of these
leaks are coming from the White
House itself,

13:13.893 --> 13:17.330 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and a division among people,
staff in the
White House...

13:17.363 --> 13:18.464 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(CROSSTALK)

13:18.498 --> 13:19.332 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: You mean from the
Trump White
House?

13:19.365 --> 13:21.267 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

13:21.301 --> 13:23.469 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ADAM SCHIFF: From the Trump
White House, exactly,
because, of course, the Trump
White House

13:23.503 --> 13:25.805 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
knew this information as well.

13:25.838 --> 13:31.177 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And there have been lots of
public reports
about how there's infighting
among the Trump

13:31.210 --> 13:33.579 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
administration and to watch your
back.

13:33.613 --> 13:38.284 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Well, maybe somebody wanted
Michael Flynn
out among the president's own
team.

13:38.317 --> 13:42.355 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
I don't know that that's
happened, but if
we're serious about this, I
would say to my

13:42.388 --> 13:46.626 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GOP colleagues, be careful what
you wish for,
because the trail may lead right
back to the

13:46.659 --> 13:48.561 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
White House.

13:48.594 --> 13:52.231 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Congressman Adam
Schiff, the
ranking member of the House
Intelligence Committee,

13:52.265 --> 13:53.232 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
thank you.

13:53.266 --> 13:54.467 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And we will be talking to you
again, I know.

13:54.500 --> 13:55.468 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

13:55.501 --> 13:57.203 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
ADAM SCHIFF: Thank you.

13:57.236 --> 14:00.506 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: In a moment, we
will hear from
Republican Senator Charles
Grassley.

14:00.540 --> 14:04.744 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, first, we want to turn to
that other
major story today, day one of
the confirmation

14:04.777 --> 14:08.681 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
hearings for Neil Gorsuch,
President Trump's
pick for the Supreme Court.

14:08.715 --> 14:13.453 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Here are some excerpts of what
senators on
the Judiciary Committee, as well
as the nominee

14:13.486 --> 14:15.421 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
himself, had to say in opening
statements.

14:15.455 --> 14:17.056 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

14:17.090 --> 14:19.726 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHARLES GRASSLEY (R), Iowa:
Judge, welcome
to the Senate Judiciary
Committee.

14:19.759 --> 14:24.964 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: It was day one of
Judge Neil
Gorsuch's hearing, as senators
took turns

14:24.997 --> 14:30.136 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
making opening statements, and
laying out
partisan attacks for the week to
come.

14:30.169 --> 14:34.574 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Judiciary Chairman Chuck
Grassley opened with
an alert for the nominee.

14:34.607 --> 14:36.342 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

14:36.375 --> 14:39.045 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CHARLES GRASSLEY: Judge, I'm
afraid, over
the next couple of days, you
will get some

14:39.078 --> 14:43.182 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
questions that will cause you
just to scratch
your head.

14:43.216 --> 14:48.054 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Senators will cite some opinion
of yours,
and then we will hear that
you're for the

14:48.087 --> 14:51.290 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
big guy and against the little
guy.

14:51.324 --> 14:56.028 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Gorsuch's record
on corporate
cases was a theme that carried
through the

14:56.062 --> 14:57.029 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
day.

14:57.063 --> 14:58.865 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

14:58.898 --> 14:59.866 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SHELDON WHITEHOUSE (D), Rhode
Island: Your
record on corporate vs. human
litigants comes

14:59.899 --> 15:03.936 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in, by one count, at 21-2 for
corporations.

15:03.970 --> 15:08.341 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Tellingly, big special interests
and their
front groups are spending
millions of dollars

15:08.374 --> 15:11.611 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in a dark money campaign to push
your confirmation.

15:11.644 --> 15:13.479 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

15:13.513 --> 15:17.150 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFF FLAKE (R), Arizona: One of
my colleagues
said Judge Gorsuch is
pro-business or against

15:17.183 --> 15:19.085 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the little guy.

15:19.118 --> 15:23.689 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think the record shows that we
can be confident
he will read the law as written
and not legislate

15:23.723 --> 15:25.525 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
from the bench.

15:25.558 --> 15:28.761 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: For their part,
Republicans
spent most of the hearing
praising Gorsuch's

15:28.795 --> 15:29.996 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
legal resume.

15:30.029 --> 15:31.464 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

15:31.497 --> 15:33.299 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ORRIN HATCH (R), Utah: Judge
Gorsuch's legal
experience is well-known.

15:33.332 --> 15:39.238 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
My Democratic colleagues have
referred to
the American Bar Association's
rating as the

15:39.272 --> 15:43.509 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
gold standard for evaluating
judicial nominees.

15:43.543 --> 15:49.749 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The ABA's unanimous
well-qualified rating
for Judge Gorsuch confirms that
he has the

15:49.782 --> 15:57.490 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
highest level of professional
qualifications,
including integrity, confidence
and temperament.

15:57.523 --> 16:02.762 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: While Democrats
knocked his
constitutional philosophy as too
rigid.

16:02.795 --> 16:04.697 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

16:04.730 --> 16:07.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
DIANNE FEINSTEIN (D),
California: Judge Gorsuch
has also stated that he believes
judges should

16:07.266 --> 16:14.607 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
look to the original public
meaning of the
Constitution when they decide
what a provision

16:14.640 --> 16:17.476 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
of the Constitution means.

16:17.510 --> 16:25.117 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This is personal, but I find
this originalist
judicial philosophy to be really
troubling.

16:25.151 --> 16:32.925 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I firmly believe the American
Constitution
is a living document, intended
to evolve as

16:32.959 --> 16:34.260 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
our country evolves.

16:34.293 --> 16:37.263 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Republican
Senator Mike Lee
pushed back.

16:37.296 --> 16:38.764 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

16:38.798 --> 16:42.034 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MIKE LEE (R), Utah: Referring to
you as an
originalist just doesn't stick.

16:42.068 --> 16:46.239 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This is not a description that
was attributed
to you.

16:46.272 --> 16:52.211 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The last time you stood before
this committee
and went through a confirmation
process, nowhere

16:52.245 --> 16:55.181 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in the record is there any
reference to you
being outside the mainstream.

16:55.214 --> 17:00.987 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: All this amidst a
bitter backdrop
for Democrats, after Republicans
last year

17:01.020 --> 17:07.627 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
blocked Merrick Garland,
President Obama's
pick to replace the late Justice
Antonin Scalia.

17:07.660 --> 17:10.029 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
His seat has now been vacant for
more than
a year.

17:10.062 --> 17:11.731 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

17:11.764 --> 17:13.165 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
RICHARD DURBIN (D-IL), Minority
Whip: It was
clear that Senator McConnell was
making a

17:13.199 --> 17:17.403 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
political decision, hoping a
Republican president
would be elected.

17:17.436 --> 17:21.707 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He was willing to ignore the
tradition and
precedent of the Senate, so that
you could

17:21.741 --> 17:23.609 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
sit at this witness table today.

17:23.643 --> 17:28.614 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Fellow Coloradan
Democrat Senator
Michael Bennet, who helped
introduced Gorsuch,

17:28.648 --> 17:29.615 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
acknowledged the tension.

17:29.649 --> 17:31.417 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

17:31.450 --> 17:33.920 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MICHAEL BENNET (D), Colorado: I
believe the
Senate has a constitutional duty
to give fair

17:33.953 --> 17:39.692 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
consideration to this nominee,
just as we
had a duty to consider fairly
Judge Merrick

17:39.725 --> 17:40.826 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Garland.

17:40.860 --> 17:43.229 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But, Mr. Chairman, two wrongs
never make a
right.

17:43.262 --> 17:46.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Some Democrats
also aimed their
attacks at President Trump.

17:46.799 --> 17:48.768 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

17:48.801 --> 17:51.771 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
RICHARD BLUMENTHAL (D),
Connecticut: The independence
of those judges has never been
more threatened

17:51.804 --> 17:54.106 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and never more important.

17:54.140 --> 17:58.945 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And a large part of the threat
comes from
the man who nominated you.

17:58.978 --> 18:03.983 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: As for the
nominee, himself,
he spoke last, giving an opening
statement

18:04.016 --> 18:05.952 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of his own, and promising
independence.

18:05.985 --> 18:09.188 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NEIL GORSUCH, Supreme Court
Nominee: Mr. Chairman,
these days, we sometimes hear
judges cynically

18:09.221 --> 18:13.859 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
described as politicians in
robes, seeking
to enforce their own politics,
rather than

18:13.893 --> 18:15.628 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
striving to apply the law
impartially.

18:15.661 --> 18:18.864 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
If I thought that were true, I
would hang
up the robe.

18:18.898 --> 18:23.035 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Gorsuch tried to
deflect some
of the claims made by Democrats.

18:23.069 --> 18:27.473 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NEIL GORSUCH: My decisions have
never reflected
a judgment about the people
before me, only

18:27.506 --> 18:33.679 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a judgment about the law and the
facts at
issue in each particular case.

18:33.713 --> 18:41.887 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A good judge can promise no more
than that,
and a good judge should
guarantee no less,

18:41.921 --> 18:46.292 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
