51:33.357 --> 51:36.994 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DANIELA EDBURG, Artist: I have
always had
this thing of being, like, of
two places.

51:37.027 --> 51:37.995 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Literally.

51:38.028 --> 51:39.196 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I mean, that's how you grew up.

51:39.229 --> 51:41.131 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
DANIELA EDBURG: Yes.

51:41.165 --> 51:46.203 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That's how I grew up, you know,
with two languages,
two points of reference
culturally that are

51:46.236 --> 51:49.406 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
similar, but not the same.

51:49.440 --> 51:55.713 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In my adulthood, I have found it
very comforting
to find connections between the
places through

51:55.746 --> 51:57.548 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
